    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="848"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d848">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">346B.115 Standard Oil Co./38</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fish</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">Saudi Arabian Series No. 8</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-24">January 24,
                            1941</date>.<lb/>[Received March 12.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the Department’s
                    telegram No. 127 of October 24, 7 p.m., 1940, and subsequent correspondence
                    regarding an attack by Italian aircraft on American oil installations in Saudi
                    Arabia and Bahrein and to enclose a copy of the English translation <pb
                        facs="0736" n="727" xml:id="pg_727"/> of a note dated January 13, 1941, from
                    the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, in reply to the
                    Legation’s note no. 15 of November 30, 1940,<note n="52" xml:id="d848fn52"
                        >Legation’s note of November 30, 1940, and Saudi Arabian note of January 13,
                        1941, not printed.</note> in which the Legation renewed its request to be
                    advised of the attitude of the Government of Saudi Arabia in respect of the
                    violation of its neutral rights as a result of the bombing of the property of
                    the California Arabian Standard Oil Company at Al Khobar.</p>
                <p>It will be noted that the Saudi Arabian Government expresses its appreciation of
                    the interest shown by the United States Government in this matter and the steps
                    taken by it in that regard. The note adds that the Saudi Arabian Government
                    presented an official protest to the Italian Government regarding the attack and
                    that the latter expressed its regret for the incident giving as an explanation
                    that the bombing was the result of an error by an Italian pilot.</p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bert Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
